The Strongsville pet owner was left 'looking uncomfortable' as she sat in a hot car in Ohio .
She filed a report against an officer who told her to sit in her hot car with the windows up and ignition off .
Last year, Shelly Nicholas was told to sit inside the hot car after a dog was found inside with no ventilation in 90 degree heat .
In Truth or Consequences, the American Veterinary Medical Association says officers have reason for concern in these situations .